<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>OpenOB WebUI</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="${request.static_url('webui:static/bootstrap.min.css')}" type="text/css" media="screen" charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="${request.static_url('webui:static/global.css')}" type="text/css" media="screen" charset="utf-8" />
    <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript" src="${request.static_url('webui:static/jquery-1.7.1.min.js')}"></script>
    <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript" src="${request.static_url('webui:static/jquery.sparkline.min.js')}"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="container">
      <div id="header">
        <a href="/">OpenOB</a>
      </div>
      <div id="content">
        <div class="hero-unit">
          <h1>Welcome to OpenOB</h1>
          <p>Open source low-latency audio transport</p>
          <p>Ready to get started?</p>
        </div>
        <h1>Configuration Server</h1>
        <p>Before OpenOB can be used you must select the configuration server to be used for this node's links.</p>
        <p>This server is used to transport configuration information between the transmitter and the receiver, and to share statekeeping information between nodes.</p>
        <p>Multiple nodes can share a configuration server so long as different configuration names are used for each link.</p>
        <form action="/save_confighost" method="POST">
          <div class="parameter">
            <strong>Configuration Server</strong>
            <input type="text" name="configuration_host" value="${static_conf['configuration_host']}" /> <input type="submit" value="Set Configuration Host" class="btn-primary" />
            <p class="help">The IP address or hostname of the configuration host for this OpenOB installation. This must be pointing at a host which has a Redis server listening on the appropriate address at the default port.</p>
          </div>
          
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="footer">
      <a href="https://github.com/JamesHarrison/openob">Open Outside Broadcast</a> - Web Interface - BETA
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
